column4: <content>Adoration, London. The figures in the border of the old King's Robe claimed by Münz, Drawings (p. 25, fig. 23) as the 4 Elements. This claim partly rejected by M. Davies, Early Netherl[andish] School (Nat[ional Gall[ery] Catalogues), 3rd.ed., 1968, p. 21:' this seems not clearly established'? (see also reprod[uced] in my Bruegel, Paintings, 3rd edition, 1973, pl. 83; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. There seems rather a connection with the zodiac: Sol in centre with Aquarius on the left- but what do the other figures represent?</content>
